
[1]tre

   SALTPE'TER,'TRE, n. [salt and Gr. stone.] A neutral salt formed by the
   nitric acid in combination with potash, and hence denominated nitrate
   of potash. It is found native in the East Indies, in Spain, in Naples
   and other places. It is also found on walls sheltered from rain, and it
   is extracted by lixiviation from the earths under cellars, stables and
   barns, &c.
